import java.net.;

public class client {

public static void main(String[] args) throws IOException {

String host = "localhost"; //Server to establish connection with.

int port = 43595; //Port used to establish connection. Default = 43595.

int timeout = 1000; //Time client waits for response from server. Default = 1000, 1 second.

   try {
 Socket sock = new Socket();
 sock.bind(null);
 sock.connect(new InetSocketAddress(host, port), timeout);
 System.out.println("Established connection with "+host+":"+port);
 sock.close();
 System.out.println("Connection closed");
}
   catch (ConnectException e) {
System.out.println("Unable to connect");
}
}

}[/code]

*/

import java.net.;
import java.io.;
import java.util.*;

public class server {

public static void main(String[] args) throws IOException {

    int connections = 0;
    ServerSocket serverSocket = null;
int port = 0;

   try {
     File f = new File("./../config.ini");
       if (!f.exists()) {
         System.out.println("Error: config.ini does not exist!");
        }
     Properties p = new Properties();
     p.load(new FileInputStream("./../config.ini"));
     port = Integer.parseInt(p.getProperty("Port").trim());
    }
   catch (Exception e) {
     System.out.println("Error: Could not load settings from config.ini:");
     e.printStackTrace();
    }

   try {
 serverSocket = new ServerSocket(port);
}
   catch (IOException e) {
 System.err.println("Could not start dummy server on port "+port);
}

 System.out.println("Dummy server started on port "+port);

 Socket clientSocket = null;

    while (clientSocket == clientSocket) {
  clientSocket = serverSocket.accept();
  clientSocket.close();

    if (connections <= 20) {
      System.out.print(".");
      connections++;
     }
        else {
      System.out.print("\n");
      connections = 0;
     }
     }

    System.out.println("Server terminated.");
    serverSocket.close();
}

}[/code]

@echo off cd .\src\ javac *.java move *.class .\..\bin\ echo If no errors are shown above, the source compiled. Hit any key to continue. pause > null

@echo off color 0a title Server cd .\bin\ java server

@echo off color 0a title Client cd .\bin\ :loop java client goto loop pause
